  "prompt": "What marks and rank is required to get Aerospace Engineering in IIT Bombay in JEE Advanced 2017?",
  "response": "As of 2017, **IIT Bombay did not offer a dedicated Bachelor of Technology (B.Tech) program in Aerospace Engineering**. IIT Bombay is renowned for its strong engineering programs in various disciplines such as Mechanical Engineering, Electrical Engineering, Computer Science, and others. If you're specifically interested in Aerospace Engineering, you might consider other Indian Institutes of Technology (IITs) that offer specialized programs in this field.\n\n### Alternative IITs Offering Aerospace Engineering\n\nSeveral IITs provide dedicated Aerospace Engineering programs, including:\n\n- **IIT Kanpur**\n- **IIT Madras**\n- **IIT Kharagpur**\n- **IIT Roorkee**\n- **IIT Delhi**\n\n### Admission Requirements for Aerospace Engineering in IITs (Approximate for 2017)\n\nAdmission to Aerospace Engineering in these IITs through **JEE Advanced** is highly competitive. Here\u2019s a general overview of the **rank ranges** that were typically required for admission into Aerospace Engineering programs around 2017:\n\n- **General Category:**\n  - **IIT Kanpur**: Rank within the top 500 to 1,000\n  - **IIT Madras**: Rank within the top 1,500 to 2,500\n  - **IIT Kharagpur**: Rank within the top 2,500 to 4,000\n  - **IIT Roorkee**: Rank within the top 3,500 to 5,500\n  - **IIT Delhi**: Occasionally offers Aerospace specializations with similar rank ranges\n\n- **Other Categories (OBC, SC/ST, etc.):**\n  - Higher rank numbers are permissible based on category-specific cutoff relaxations.\n\n### Important Considerations\n\n1. **JEE Advanced Rank:** Admission primarily depends on your JEE Advanced rank, which is influenced by your JEE Main performance, All India Rank (AIR), and category.\n\n2. **Yearly Variations:** Cutoff ranks can fluctuate each year based on factors like the difficulty level of the exam, number of applicants, and seat availability.\n\n3. **Reservation Policies:** Indian Institutes of Technology follow reservation policies as per government guidelines, which can affect cutoff ranks for different categories.\n\n4. **Integrated Programs:** Some IITs may offer integrated M.Tech or dual-degree programs in Aerospace Engineering, which might have different admission criteria.\n\n### Recommendations\n\n- **Check Official Sources:** For the most accurate and detailed information, refer to the [official JEE Advanced 2017 cutoff data](https://jeeadv.ac.in/) and the respective IIT admission brochures from 2017.\n\n- **Explore Related Disciplines:** If Aerospace Engineering is not available, consider related fields like Mechanical Engineering or Engineering Physics, which offer electives or specializations in aerospace-related subjects.\n\n- **Prepare Thoroughly:** Given the competitiveness, ensure a strong preparation strategy for both JEE Main and JEE Advanced to secure a favorable rank.\n\nIf you have any more questions or need guidance on preparing for IIT admissions, feel free to ask!",
